			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				Finished it last night. The ending had me seeing red. It was a Matrix-II ending... where it simply ends in the MIDDLE of an ongoing story. I f'ing HATE that @#%$. There will definitely be a Halo III. -1 for @#%$ half-complete ending! Only a 9/10. It could also be that to see a real ending one must beat it on Legendary. That's going to take me a LONG time. Heroic in Halo II is slightly harder than Legendary was in Halo I. Legendary in Halo II also doubles the number of spawns and/or attack waves in any given location. My hat is off to anyone who can beat it on Legendary. Forget about the Co-op respawn tricks... if anyone dies in Co-op, EVERYONE respawns immediately from the last checkpoint. You gotta do it right this time.
<br />

<br />
There were some parts towards the end that were straight out of Doom 3. Good times. If you shoot down a flood creature, the little facehuggers that chase you around will hop on it and resurrect it. That's a cool change.
<br />

<br />
The pistol is @#%$ in Halo II. Even dual wielding them, and firing two charge-shots at once, is just barely enough to kill one of the little guys on normal. It doesn't even phase them on Legendary. I'd say it's a little too toned down now. Only good for pistol-whipping. Shotgun still owns, but only 36 shells instead of 50. Shock rifles (particularly, dual wielding them, or their big brother the Brute shock rifle) are the own now.
<br />

<br />
The hunters are not so easy to beat down in hand to hand anymore. They have this twirling backhand backwards attack that'll lay you out flat if you try to attack them from behind. Much more challenging, and physical hits don't bother them as much. You really need to use heavy weapons on them now.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
		</table>
		</td>
