				<div class="postbody">
				D'oh, ok, after checking, Halo II only supports 2-player co-op. The menu leads you to believe otherwise, until you actually try to start it with more than two and it gives you a complaint. You can do 4-player custom games as usual though.
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://games.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=04/10/15/1837204&amp;tid=211&amp;tid=1" target="_blank" class="postlink">You can read all the gory details about the "early release" here, as well as Bungie's official statement.</a>
<br />

<br />
Someone at the manufacturing plant undoubtedly pilfered a copy. Bungie is having the typical "sky is falling" reaction, at least publically. It's all over every filesharing network on the planet. It's no beta. It's the full game, gold copy. It just happens to be the french version, so all the spoken dialogue is french. That gets hella annoying after a while, though it is funny hearing the soldiers cursing in french. I hear "cabron" a lot.
<br />

<br />
Can't wait to get the full game, seeing as Ron Perlman and Laura Prepon (among others) are in the voice credits. Seems like they went all out on this one.<br />
