			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				Four controller slots. They are really nothing but funky-shaped USB ports. Have only done 2-player multiplayer in Halo II.
<br />

<br />
Before you go out and spend a lot of money on a new one, consider this.
<br />

<br />
1. Buy a refurb ($100 in most places).
<br />
2. Buy a ~200GB HDD (Seagate 200GB is $114 w 5yr/warranty).
<br />
3. Buy a Xenium Modchip ($60).
<br />
4. Buy a PS/2 Mouse/Keyboard adapter for one of the controller ports ($30).
<br />
5. Download Slayer's EVOX from suprnova.org and burn a CD of it (free).
<br />

<br />
Refurb Xbox is a fancy way of saying, "It had a failed hard disk." It's just a P3-733MHz PC under the hood. Take 3 hours, install the mod chip, install Slayer's EVOX, and now you have a Media Player PC that happens to be able to play and rip Xbox games and emulate everything older than the Sega Dreamcast. It'll play DVDs and do web browsing on your TV.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
		</table>
		</td>
	</tr>
