			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				Halo 2 will be released worldwide on Nov 9. 
<br />

<br />
The multiplayer on Halo 2 is revamped, there is alot of new moves. However much to the benefit of the game, features like peeking corners and sprinting have been taken out. The game is too fast paced to peak, and spriting is a no go. Also, no more health packs you have a shield and it's recharges pretty fast, mastering when to duck and recharge is going to be vital.
<br />

<br />
Destructable vehicles is one of the best features here, It's pure genius.  Someone getting away? instead of shooting the general car, aim for the tires and baam it falls off.
<br />

<br />
New guns, pistol has been nerfed, no more zoom on it, however it seems like the battle rifle will be the new pistol here. Powerups can be turned on and off, respawn time on weapons can be set to random, no more timers.
<br />

<br />
I'm not going to spoil the new weapons or the new levels, but one of the best levels i've played in a FPS is lockout, period. They are brining back old levels from Halo, such as hang em high, blood gultch, and maybe chillout and sidewinder, not too sure.
<br />

<br />
IF you have an Xbox there is no justifible reason not to buy this game.
<br />

<br />
Edit: Rav yes, Heroic and Legendary(probably just Legendary) ending sequences according to Bungie tradition will be different from the original, i'm doubting the making of Halo 3 here. I believe they either included another level to finish it up in legendary or an alternate ending sequence wrapping it all up. I think i've read somewhere Bungie stating there will not be a Halo 3, I could be wrong, i'll try and find it.
<br />

<br />

<br />
10 out of 10.<br />
				<span class="gensmall"></span><br />
				</div>
			</td></tr>
